<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="392" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,475,1149]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1835" box="[151,274,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Notocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,274,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="392">Notocyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was revised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A." box="[460,741,475,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="71 - 78" refId="ref10755" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A. (1992) Descriptions of new species of Notocyrtus Burmeister, 1835 (Hemiptera-Heteroptera, Reduviidae; Harpactorinae). Anais da Academia Brasileira de Ciencias, 64, 71 - 78." type="journal article" year="1992">Carvalho &amp; Costa (1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A." box="[754,813,475,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="365 - 384" refId="ref10805" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A. (1993) Revision of the known species of Notocyrtus Burmeister, 1835 (Hemiptera-Heteroptera, Reduviidae; Harpactorinae). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 53, 365 - 384." type="journal article" year="1993">1993</bibRefCitation>
), with further descriptions of three species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Costa, L. A. A." pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref11867" refString="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Costa, L. A. A. (2001) Descricao de uma especie nova de Notocyrtus Burmeister, 1835, do estado de Rondonia, Brasil (Hemiptera, Reduviidae, Harpactorinae). Boletim do Museu Nacional, Nova Serie, Zoologia, 452, 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2001">Costa &amp; Gil-Santana (2001)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Costa, L. A. A." box="[385,707,511,537]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref11867" refString="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Costa, L. A. A. (2001) Descricao de uma especie nova de Notocyrtus Burmeister, 1835, do estado de Rondonia, Brasil (Hemiptera, Reduviidae, Harpactorinae). Boletim do Museu Nacional, Nova Serie, Zoologia, 452, 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2001">Gil-Santana &amp; Costa (2001)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Forero, D." box="[766,1102,511,537]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="55 - 67" refId="ref11926" refString="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Forero, D. (2009) A new species of Notocyrtus, a new synonym of Coilopus, and new records and notes on other Harpactorini (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Reduviidae: Harpactorinae) from South America. Zootaxa, 2148 (1), 55 - 67. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2148.1.5" type="journal article" year="2009">Gil-Santana &amp; Forero (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, resulting in 24 current valid species in the genus, among which only 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[604,977,547,574]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Notocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fornicatus">
<emphasis box="[604,847,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="392">Notocyrtus fornicatus</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1201,1366,547,573]" name="French Guiana" pageId="11" pageNumber="392">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
so far (
<bibRefCitation author="Maldonado, J. C." box="[159,355,583,609]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" refId="ref13244" refString="Maldonado, J. C. (1990) Systematic catalogue of the Reduviidae of the World. Caribbean Journal of Science, Special publication No. 1. University of Puerto Rico, Mayaguez, 694 pp." type="book" year="1990">Maldonado 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A." box="[367,639,583,609]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="71 - 78" refId="ref10755" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A. (1992) Descriptions of new species of Notocyrtus Burmeister, 1835 (Hemiptera-Heteroptera, Reduviidae; Harpactorinae). Anais da Academia Brasileira de Ciencias, 64, 71 - 78." type="journal article" year="1992">Carvalho &amp; Costa 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A." box="[651,711,583,609]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="365 - 384" refId="ref10805" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A. (1993) Revision of the known species of Notocyrtus Burmeister, 1835 (Hemiptera-Heteroptera, Reduviidae; Harpactorinae). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 53, 365 - 384." type="journal article" year="1993">1993</bibRefCitation>
). Taxonomical notes, new records of occurrences to other countries and observations about the biology of some species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1835" box="[814,937,619,644]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Notocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[814,937,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="392">Notocyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gil-Santana, H. R." box="[1145,1353,619,645]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="59 - 68" refId="ref11723" refString="Gil-Santana, H. R. (2007) New records of Reduviidae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera) from Brazil. Zootaxa, 1390 (1), 59 - 68. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1390.1.7" type="journal article" year="2007">Gil-Santana (2007</bibRefCitation>
, 2008), 
<bibRefCitation author="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Forero, D." box="[151,477,655,681]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="55 - 67" refId="ref11926" refString="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Forero, D. (2009) A new species of Notocyrtus, a new synonym of Coilopus, and new records and notes on other Harpactorini (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Reduviidae: Harpactorinae) from South America. Zootaxa, 2148 (1), 55 - 67. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2148.1.5" type="journal article" year="2009">Gil-Santana &amp; Forero (2009)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Alvarez, L. J. &amp; Zamudio, F. &amp; Melo, M. C." box="[530,766,655,681]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="20195927" refId="ref10463" refString="Alvarez, L. J., Zamudio, F. &amp; Melo, M. C. (2019) Eating with the enemy? Mimic complex between a stingless bee and assassin bugs. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 59, e 20195927. https: // doi. org / 10.11606 / 1807 - 0205 / 2019.59.27" type="journal article" year="2019">
Alvarez 
<emphasis box="[625,675,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="392">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,475,1149]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1835" box="[325,448,691,716]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Notocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[325,448,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="392">Notocyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been recognized as mimetics of meliponine bees (
<bibRefCitation author="Haviland, M. D." box="[1085,1256,691,717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="129 - 154" refId="ref12522" refString="Haviland, M. D. (1931) The Reduviidae of Kartabo Bartica District, British Guiana. Zoologica, 7, 129 - 154. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / p. 203764" type="journal article" year="1931">Haviland 1931</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jackson, J. F." box="[1269,1432,691,717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="200 - 202" refId="ref12591" refString="Jackson, J. F. (1973) Mimicry of Trigona bees by a reduviid (Hemiptera) from British Honduras. Florida Entomologist, 56, 200 - 202. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3493124" type="journal article" year="1973">Jackson, 1973</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Roubik, D. W." box="[151,299,727,753]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" refId="ref13499" refString="Roubik, D. W. (1989) Ecology and natural history of tropical bees. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, 514 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / CBO 9780511574641" type="book" year="1989">Roubik 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gil-Santana, H. R." box="[310,510,727,753]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="43 - 53" refId="ref11767" refString="Gil-Santana, H. R. (2008) New records, and nomenclatural and biological notes on Reduviidae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera) from Bolivia and Brazil. Zootaxa, 1785 (1), 43 - 53. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1785.1.2" type="journal article" year="2008">Gil-Santana 2008</bibRefCitation>
), in which the mimicry is enhanced by an inflated pronotum (
<bibRefCitation author="Haviland, M. D." box="[1196,1365,727,753]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="129 - 154" refId="ref12522" refString="Haviland, M. D. (1931) The Reduviidae of Kartabo Bartica District, British Guiana. Zoologica, 7, 129 - 154. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / p. 203764" type="journal article" year="1931">Haviland 1931</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jackson, J. F." pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="200 - 202" refId="ref12591" refString="Jackson, J. F. (1973) Mimicry of Trigona bees by a reduviid (Hemiptera) from British Honduras. Florida Entomologist, 56, 200 - 202. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3493124" type="journal article" year="1973">Jackson 1973</bibRefCitation>
). Some species of this genus are variable in color, particularly of the pronotum, which may be a result of mimicking different meliponine bees in different localities (
<bibRefCitation author="Jackson, J. F." box="[819,976,799,825]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="200 - 202" refId="ref12591" refString="Jackson, J. F. (1973) Mimicry of Trigona bees by a reduviid (Hemiptera) from British Honduras. Florida Entomologist, 56, 200 - 202. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3493124" type="journal article" year="1973">Jackson 1973</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Alvarez, L. J. &amp; Zamudio, F. &amp; Melo, M. C." box="[994,1227,799,825]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="20195927" refId="ref10463" refString="Alvarez, L. J., Zamudio, F. &amp; Melo, M. C. (2019) Eating with the enemy? Mimic complex between a stingless bee and assassin bugs. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 59, e 20195927. https: // doi. org / 10.11606 / 1807 - 0205 / 2019.59.27" type="journal article" year="2019">
Alvarez 
<emphasis box="[1090,1139,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="392">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded a “plantreduviid-bee”, interaction involving species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1835" box="[692,815,835,860]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Notocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[692,815,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="392">Notocyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, hypothesizing about the functionality of the mimetic complexes described by them.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="392" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,475,1149]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392">
The structure of the head, shape of the pronotum and tibiae, and, to a lesser extent, the color patterns were emphasized as good features for separating species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1835" box="[728,851,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Notocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[728,851,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="392">Notocyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A." box="[894,1173,943,969]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="71 - 78" refId="ref10755" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A. (1992) Descriptions of new species of Notocyrtus Burmeister, 1835 (Hemiptera-Heteroptera, Reduviidae; Harpactorinae). Anais da Academia Brasileira de Ciencias, 64, 71 - 78." type="journal article" year="1992">Carvalho &amp; Costa (1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A." box="[1184,1244,943,969]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="365 - 384" refId="ref10805" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. &amp; Costa, L. A. A. (1993) Revision of the known species of Notocyrtus Burmeister, 1835 (Hemiptera-Heteroptera, Reduviidae; Harpactorinae). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 53, 365 - 384." type="journal article" year="1993">1993</bibRefCitation>
). Concerning the male genitalia, these authors only described the parameres, some of which were considered among the diagnostic characteristics of some species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,475,1149]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392">
New figures of the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Costa &amp; Gil-Santana, 2001" authorityName="Costa &amp; Gil-Santana" authorityYear="2001" box="[612,1043,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Notocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibanae">
<emphasis box="[612,729,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="392">N. tibanae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Costa, L. A. A." box="[736,1043,1051,1077]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref11867" refString="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Costa, L. A. A. (2001) Descricao de uma especie nova de Notocyrtus Burmeister, 1835, do estado de Rondonia, Brasil (Hemiptera, Reduviidae, Harpactorinae). Boletim do Museu Nacional, Nova Serie, Zoologia, 452, 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2001">Costa &amp; Gil-Santana, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, more detailed than those provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Costa, L. A. A." box="[187,506,1087,1113]" pageId="11" pageNumber="392" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref11867" refString="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Costa, L. A. A. (2001) Descricao de uma especie nova de Notocyrtus Burmeister, 1835, do estado de Rondonia, Brasil (Hemiptera, Reduviidae, Harpactorinae). Boletim do Museu Nacional, Nova Serie, Zoologia, 452, 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2001">Costa &amp; Gil-Santana (2001)</bibRefCitation>
, are presented to improve the knowledge of the male genital structures in this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
